24/08/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- The exact date of November's local and parliamentary elections will be announced early next month, if it does not harm ongoing efforts to resolve Kosovo's final status, UNMIK chief Joachim Ruecker and Kosovo President Fatmir Sejdiu announced after their meeting Thursday (August 23rd). Ruecker accepted the recommendations of the Kosovo negotiating team, including that leaders of municipalities be chosen through direct elections. 
In other news Thursday, the OSCE published a report on the municipalities' legislative activities. OSCE mission chief in Kosovo, Ambassador Werner Wnendt, said the organisation's goal is to help strengthen Kosovo's institutions by applying the legal framework and the principles of good governance. (Telegrafi, RTK, QIK - 23/08/07)
